author: Nexcell Pride
text:
Started with "Be Happy" (Ucchii0-sama) and the complete intro, the LiveChat at white characters and the Supaachaato Orei Time with the room at sunset and the complete message at top...

These elements indicated she was using her laptop for a while.
Maybe she's trespassing her stuff at her Desktop PC (Where has the prototype version of intro from January 2020 and new configurations), but still using laptop for special moments. :_るんるん:

Wow, also was an accidented stream due to some gurugurus and battery low in one part (At second song), but successfully restored.

The first song "Kingyo Hanabi" finally was sung accurately.
At Million's endurance, that song was the second from that "setori" (Set List), but she couldn't sing due to huge tearful emotion at that moment (She reached the million before singing and tried to sing, even crying) :_ハート:
That song needs a PV. Along with "Iris" (Original), she has only "Hana ni Bourei" cover, which reached over 4000000 views. :_ちょうちょ:

And normal stream had a Zatsudan part about complex terms...

And Supaachaato Orei Time, she read also the previous streams' superchats.
And in some parts, Akai Naisupa rains and later Heart floods were present. 
Wow... Clearly a Mission Accomplished. We restored her smile. :_ハート:

Personal Postscript: I haven't defined personal marks for some reason... I'll try to watch and catch the special marks later. Gomen ne :_あせり:

author: Redan Kenneth Uy
text:
スーパーチャットリーディングで私の長いメッセージを読まずにいてくれてありがとう。私はわざと早朝に送りすぎて、気付いて読んでくれる人が少なすぎるようにしています。いつも忘れないでください。私たちは常にあなたをサポートします。どんなことがあっても。 Thank you for not reading my long message in superchat reading. I intentionally send them too early in the morning so that too few can notice and read it. Always remember. We will always here to support you. No matter what happens.

とにかく、私はもう眠らなければなりません。どうか夜更かししないでくださいね。それではまた明日、お会いしましょう。おやすみなさい。いい夢を見てね。 Anyway, I have to go and sleep now. Please don't stay up late. See you tomorrow. Goodnight. Sweet dreams.
